    {
      "id": "PopularPost30246",
      "post_content": "I don't know multiplayer, but this looks like a waste in any form of two-player Constructed. Hopefully most things you damage in that environment die anyway, so including an expensive and invested card just to make sure of this is of extremely limited use. In Limited, on the other hand, this is an excellent way to stall the ground - you should be very hesitant to attack an opponent with Death Pits if there's any possibility of being blocked, since it enables some extremely unbalanced trades. Of course, in theory this effect is symmetrical - but in practise, the person playing Death Pits knew he was doing so and had a chance to build a deck to take advantage of it, and the other guy didn't. Especially powerful in Limited with something like Prodigal Sorcerer, of course.",
      "posted_by": "jeff-heikkinen",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost30246\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">I don't know multiplayer, but this looks like a waste in any form of two-player Constructed. Hopefully most things you damage in that environment die anyway, so including an expensive and invested card just to make sure of this is of extremely limited use. In Limited, on the other hand, this is an excellent way to stall the ground - you should be very hesitant to attack an opponent with Death Pits if there's any possibility of being blocked, since it enables some extremely unbalanced trades. Of course, in theory this effect is symmetrical - but in practise, the person playing Death Pits knew he was doing so and had a chance to build a deck to take advantage of it, and the other guy didn't. Especially powerful in Limited with something like Prodigal Sorcerer, of course.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '30246'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy1097\">jeff-heikkinen</span>\r\n                                (10/17/2009 1:24:57 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"f